Class StateValues

  • java.lang.Object
    • explicit.StateValues
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    StateVector

    public class StateValues
extends java.lang.Object
implements StateVector
    Class for explicit-state storage of a state-indexed vector of values (int, double, boolean).

    • Method Detail

      • createFromIntegerArray

        public static StateValues createFromIntegerArray(int[] array,
                                                 Model model)
        Create a new (int-valued) state values vector from an existing array of ints. The array is stored directly, not copied. Also set associated model (whose state space size should match vector size).

      • createFromDoubleArray

        public static StateValues createFromDoubleArray(double[] array,
                                                Model model)
        Create a new (double-valued) state values vector from an existing array of doubles. The array is stored directly, not copied. Also set associated model (whose state space size should match vector size).

      • createFromBitSet

        public static StateValues createFromBitSet(java.util.BitSet bs,
                                           Model model)
        Create a new (Boolean-valued) state values vector from an existing BitSet. The BitSet is stored directly, not copied. Also set associated model (and this determines the vector size).

      • createFromBitSetAsDoubles

        public static StateValues createFromBitSetAsDoubles(java.util.BitSet bitset,
                                                    Model model)
        Create a new (double-valued) state values vector from a BitSet, where each entry is 1.0 if in the bitset, 0.0 otherwise. Also set associated model (and this determines the vector size). The bitset is not modified or stored.
